<h1>Problem 2147 - 1998 IMOSL, N7, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Prove that for each positive integer \(n\), there exists a positive integer with the following properties: It has exactly \(n\) digits. None of the digits is 0. It is divisible by the sum of its digits.</p>
